        = image_tag "http://placehold.it/150x150"
      .product-point-info
        %h3 Handwoven in Peru
        %p Each strap is handwoven by artisans in Peru. The artisans apply traditional weaving techniques that have been passed down for generations. Most of the artisans are women who work from home with their children playing nearby.
    .product-point
      .product-point-icon
        = image_tag "http://placehold.it/150x150"
      .product-point-info
        %h3 Totally Unique
        %p Each guitar strap is as unique as the person that made it. We offer eleven patterns, but the patterns have slight variations due to the hand-crafted process. The personality of the artisan comes through making each strap one-of-a-kind.
    .product-point
      .product-point-icon
        = image_tag "http://placehold.it/150x150"
      .product-point-info
        %h3 Sustainable &amp; Fair
        %p All of our straps are made according to fair trade guidelines. The artisans earn a living wage, have a safe working environment, and are not subject to workplace pollutants or toxins. And, of course, there is no child labor.
    .product-point
      .product-point-icon
        = image_tag "http://placehold.it/150x150"
      .product-point-info
        %h3 Lifetime Guarantee
        %p This is the kind of strap you'll want to pass down to your kids. If it breaks or wears out from normal use, just send it back and we'll either fix it or replace it for you. Unless you cut it in half with scissors, this strap isn't going to break on you.

